name: Banksy Locations (& a Tour) Vol.2 - FREE UK P&P
description: DIRECT FROM THE AUTHOR..... BRAND NEW VOLUME (December 2010) - Hardback book with over 380 pages... I am the author, photographer and publisher of this unique, unofficial, & unashamedly DIY book. Free updates to the status of the graffiti in the book will periodically be made available on my website - www.shellshockpublishing.co.uk - once I get the site going again. Until then I can email you all three of the free updates, which are now available in one huge 38 page PDF. Updates can save you a long walk if you are planning to visit the sites and they have since gone. They also give full info on new pieces done since the book was printed. 12% of my sale price on these sales will be donated to three charitable organisations - Bristol Mind, Ben's Centre, and merls [change]. For all sales I will chuck in a couple of rare A6 postcard flyers for the book. They are great for geeky collectors like me, or can actually be sent to a friend - you can do my job for me basically :-) PLEASE NOTE - Just to be clear this book is TOTALLY new - nothing from Volume 1 of the book is in Vol 2. All these locations, photos, information etc are new to readers... ISBN - 978-0-9554712-3-0 Size - 128 x 175 x 28mm 382 pages, 1 x drawing, 230 x photos Recommended Retail Price - £12.50 Released - December 2010 (1st edition) Info about the book… This unique, unofficial, & unashamedly DIY book follows on from the curious runaway success of Martin Bull's first self-published book, Banksy Locations (& Tours) Vol.1, by rounding up the rest of Banksy's UK graffiti from the last five years, as well as older survivors. It includes over 135 different locations of Banksy's street graffiti, past & present (almost half of which are still worth visiting); over 230 colour photographs; information, random facts & idle chit-chat on each location; a full walking tour of his remaining work in Bristol; and also snippets of art/graffiti by Eine, Faile, Inkie, Kato, Mode 2, BA / DBZ, & Rowdy. Collect all the locations like a geek or just wander around, stop at the various quirky local attractions and explore parts you may never have visited before. Alternatively, get your slippers on, and settle back for an open-top bus ride though some of Banksy's best public work... General Information I will do my best to provide a very swift send out of goods, and will usually not take more that say 2 days to send something once payment is confirmed / cleared. I do though have a 'normal' job as well and can't always joyfully join the huge queues at the post office every day :-) Feel free to ask any questions which may help you to understand the item better. Just ask and I‘ll do my best to help. Postage and Packing P&P in the UK is free for you (it costs me about £2.70). As I also buy many things through the post and I’m a great re-user/recycler in life, so I will often recycle packing material, which keeps costs down for all of us. I will always pack items as carefully and fully as possible. For Europe please add £4.99. For elsewhere please add £9.99. Sorry, but it is a heavy, hardback book (800g). If you require extra insurance or special packing / postage requests please let me know as early as possible. For recorded delivery in the UK please just add £1.10p. Thanks for looking and happy buying. Martin

name: Banksy Locations (& Tours) Vol.1 - NEW 5th edition - FREE UK P&P
description: DIRECT FROM THE AUTHOR... 5th edition - Heavily revised and updated in late 2013 BRAND NEW EDITION OF THIS LONG RUNNING BOOK I am the author, photographer and publisher of this book. This 5th Edition was released in December 2013 and has been totally updated to include all the lastest news up to October 2013. It has also been re-written & re-designed. Extra love & peace included as well. This unique, unofficial, book was the first independent book to be published about Banksy's art & is based on the ground breaking free tours & location information that I researched & offered to the public in 2006. Those free street tours were also a first, although many imitators now offer paid for tours. Free updates to the status of the art in the book will periodically be made available on my website - www.shellshockpublishing.co.uk - (once I have got the site going again) and/or via my mailing list. Updates can save you a long walk if you are planning to visit the sites and they have since gone. For all sales I will chuck in a very rare A6 flyer which relates to the first edition in late 2006. It is now well out of date but a nice little memento and great for geeky collectors like me. PLEASE NOTE - This is a completely separate volume to my Volume 2 book. Nothing from Vol.1 is repeated in Vol.2, and vice versa. ISBN - 978-0-9554712-5-4 Size - 125 x 168 x 16mm 180 pages, 3 x drawings, 127 x photos Recommended Price - £9.50 Released - Dec 2013 (5th edition) Info about the book… A Collection of Art Locations & Photographs in London, mainly of Banksy's street work - 65 Banksy street art locations, past & present - Information, random facts & idle chit-chat on each location - Over 125 colour photographs - Also includes snippets of art by Eine, Faile, El Chivo, Arofish, Cept, Space Invader, D*face, Shepard Fairey / Obey Giant, & Blek Le Rat. Following the runaway success of his original self-published book, Martin Bull has now totally updated, re-written, and re-designed his best seller for this new 5th edition. This unique, unofficial, book was the first independent book to be published about Banksy's art & is based on the ground breaking free tours & location information that Martin researched & offered to the public in 2006. Those free street tours were also a first, although many imitators now offer paid for tours. A few of the locations are still holding out (& worth visiting), but the practical walking tours of the past are now the street art archaeology of tomorrow, so put your feet up & settle back for an historic open-top bus ride through some of Banksy’s best earlier work in three diverse areas of London. name: Banksy - Girl With Balloon - Black & White 10" x 8" photo, with hand coloured red balloon
description: NEW Black & Whites from my personal collection of my photos. I am doing other listings for other photos and also some for 6"x4" and 7" x 5" packs (including this image but not hand coloured), so please check those out if you prefer something a bit different to what you see here. This listing is for - 1 x Black & White photo of Banksy's most iconic image, the 'Girl With Balloon'. This was taken by me on the fringes of Hoxton, East London on 18th October 2006. It was white washed by the local housing provider in March 2007, meaning there were no longer any left in the world! I have hand coloured the balloon to its original red colour and shape / size.. This image is consistently choosen by fans (especially females) as their favourite image, and its meaning is endlessly debated on dull forums. Is the girl grabbing for the balloon (lost love?) or is she letting it go? Who cares - LOL. I would have thought it was relatively clear, as his books give the following caption, “When the time comes to leave, just walk away quietly and don't make any fuss”. Mr.B probably doesn't mention this image often to Mrs.B :-) • Size = 10" x 8" (25 x 20cm). I have deliberately choosen this size as it is the easiest large photo size to find a frame for. • Solid black border OR solid white border (use the drop-down box to choose which you want to buy) • Printed by a well known and well respected photo company on Kodak archive photo paper (sorry but these ones, at this price, are not hand-printed photos from a darkroom) Your photo will be sent in a plastic protector, within a brand new strong board backed 'Do Not Bend' envelope. I then add a piece of 1000micron board on top, so the photo is sandwiched with card on both sides. NOTE - if postage to the country where you live doesn't seem to be available at the check out please email me. Big Cartel has a rather funny / annoying postage system. I WILL post to anywhere!
